Package org.example.model.playarea

Class PlayerCardArea

java.lang.Object
org.example.model.playarea.PlayerCardArea
public class PlayerCardArea extends Object
Represents the area of a player within a card game, holding their hand, played cards, and managing interactions with game nodes.

  • Constructor Details

    • PlayerCardArea

      public PlayerCardArea()
      Constructs a new PlayerCardArea with initialized lists. This constructor initializes the PlayerCardArea by creating empty lists for available nodes, all nodes, placeholders, already used nodes, and temporary secret objectives.

      Parameters:

      alreadyUsed - the list of already used nodes
      Returns:

    • findRedGreen

      public boolean findRedGreen(PlaceHolder node, List<PlaceHolder> alreadyUsed)
      Checks for a specific pattern involving two red and green cards. This method looks for a node at the same x-coordinate and 2 units below the given node, and then checks for another node at a specific position relative to the second node with a PLANT resource. If found, it adds these nodes to the already used list.
      Parameters:
      node - the starting node
      alreadyUsed - the list of already used nodes
      Returns:
      true if the pattern is found, false otherwise

    • findGreenPurple
